description: Aspose.Imaging for .NET is an imaging library that lets developers create, edit, draw or convert images in their .NET applications. Aspose.Imaging provides features that go beyond the native capabilities of the development platform. It works independent of other applications and although Aspose.Imaging allows you to save to Adobe PhotoShop® format (PSD), you do not need PhotoShop on the machine.
releaseNotes:
New Features
IMAGING-33193:	Provided support for saving each frame of Tiff to different image format 
IMAGING-33191:	Provided support not to save changes to images until Save method is called 
IMAGING-33188:	Supported RotateFlip for Tiff file format 
IMAGING-33150:	Supported for PSD layer manipulation 
IMAGING-33144:	Reworked images for cache usage 
IMAGING-31709:	Save and Create options redesigned

Bugs Fixed
IMAGING-33206:	Fix frame removal of the frame in Tiff Image
IMAGING-33208:	Opening and saving file causing black images
